    "plan_content": "Here's the complete plan for the `next/geo` module:\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThe implementation follows the **exact same three-file pattern** as `next/server`/`userAgent`, confirmed by reading the reference files. **5 files total** — 4 created, 1 modified:\n\n### Files to Create\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts` | Core TypeScript implementation |\n| `packages/next/geo.js` | Public CJS entry point (mirrors `server.js`) |\n| `packages/next/geo.d.ts` | Type re-exports (mirrors `server.d.ts`) |\n| `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts` | Jest test suite (11 test cases) |\n\n### File to Modify\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `packages/next/package.json` | Add `\"geo.js\"` and `\"geo.d.ts\"` to `files` array after `\"form.d.ts\"` |\n\n### Key design decisions confirmed by exploration:\n- **`null → undefined` coercion**: `Headers.get()` returns `null` for missing headers; use `?? undefined` to keep return type `string | undefined` (strict-mode safe)\n- **Cloudflare fallback**: `x-vercel-ip-country ?? cf-ipcountry` — Vercel takes priority\n- **No `exports` field** in `package.json` — no need to add one, `files` array is sufficient\n- **Test framework**: Jest with `describe`/`it` blocks (confirmed by `batcher.test.ts` and `adapters/headers.test.ts` patterns)\n- **Haversine formula**: Standard implementation using Earth radius 6371 km; NYC→London distance ~5570 km ± 50 km tolerance",
